                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-defend1283" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                  </persName>
             &amp; 
               <persName id="t18280529-237-defend1284" type="defendantName">
                  CORNELIUS 
                  GLANDFIELD
               <interp inst="t18280529-237-defend1284" type="surname" value="GLANDFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-defend1284" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-defend1284" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-defend1284" type="age" value="14"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were indicted for <rs id="t18280529-237-off1300" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-off1300" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-off1300" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280529-237-cd1301" type="crimeDate">25th of May</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-237-off1300 t18280529-237-cd1301"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 2s., the goods of a 
                     <persName id="t18280529-237-victim1285" type="victimName">man unknown<interp inst="t18280529-237-victim1285" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-237-off1300 t18280529-237-victim1285"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-237-person1286">
                  CHARLES 
                  GEORGE VINCENT
               <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1286" type="surname" value="GEORGE VINCENT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1286" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1286" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On Sunday week, about half-past nine o'clock in the evening, I was in the <placeName id="t18280529-237-crimeloc1302">City-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-237-crimeloc1302" type="placeName" value="City-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-237-crimeloc1302" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-237-off1300 t18280529-237-crimeloc1302"></join>; I saw a person, who I believe was Glandfield, take a handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket, and give it to Aston, who put it under the tail of his coat, and was crossing the road, I went up to him, and took him - I put my hand down by his side, where I thought I had seen the handkerchief and endeavoured to take it from him; I felt his hand move, but did not see the handkerchief go from him; Mr. Hall came up, and asked if I had lost anything - I said I had not, but another person had picked a gentleman's pocket of his handkerchief, and given it to the prisoner; he said he had seen something thrown away, and ran and got this handkerchief - I believe Glandfield was the person<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182805290102"></xptr>who took it; I went the next morning, and took him in Chequer-place.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Was it not rather dark? A. Yes, but there was a light opposite me - a person named Toole was with me - I ordered Toole to go after the gentleman.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-237-person1287">
                  THOMAS 
                  TOOLE
               <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1287" type="surname" value="TOOLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1287" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1287" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Vincent; I told him I saw the two prisoners in company trying pockets - we followed them, and saw them go towards a gentleman; Glandfield took the handkerchief from him, and gave it to Aston; I said, "They have got it" - he crossed the road, and took Aston; I was going after Glandfield, but he said, Go, tell the gentleman - I went, but could not overtake him; I knew where Glandfield lived, and told Vincent.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-237-person1288">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HALL
               <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1288" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1288" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1288" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am inspector of the watch. I was standing at the Star public-house; I saw Vincent collar Aston; and while he had hold of him, I saw Aston throw the handkerchief down - I asked Vincent if he had lost anything; he said Aston had received a handkerchief; I told him to hold him fast - I went to the place where the handkerchief fell; a little boy took it up and gave it to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-237-person1289">
                  TIMOTHY 
                  DONOVAN
               <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1289" type="surname" value="DONOVAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1289" type="given" value="TIMOTHY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-person1289" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I picked up this handkerchief; I did not see who threw it down.</p>
               <p>ASTON'S Defence. There were two or three men in the road; the officer collared me and took me.</p>
               <p>GLANDFIELD'S Defence. I was in bed at half past eight o'clock.</p>
               <p>ASTON - <rs id="t18280529-237-verdict1303" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-verdict1303" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
               <p>GLANDFIELD - <rs id="t18280529-237-verdict1304" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-237-verdict1304" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
